IC Career Services Employer Partner Program (EPP) , employers can make a transformative impact on our career development resources while increasing their visibility on campus. EPP membership provides companies with additional business services, unique engagement opportunities, and premium visibility options that reach over 30,000 students and alumni.      Program Benefits        ANNUAL PARTNER BENEFITS    GOLD LEVEL $6,000    SILVER LEVEL $4,000    BRONZE LEVEL $2,000     Opportunity to host one “Partner Day at   UIC” each semester:  a half-day program which can include company presentation, overview,  and/or panel.   X         Recognition on UIC Today’s “Events” webpage (380,000 viewers).   X         Recognition in targeted student email blasts including description of organization and opportunities.   2 per semester    1 per semester       Sponsor recognition on campus-wide digital signage (20-30 signs).   X    X        Logo recognition on student volunteer career event apparel (20-50 volunteers per year).   X    X        Sponsor recognition, including logo and link, on the Career Services website (53,000 annual website views).   X    X    X     Prominent visibility on Career Services' donor recognition wall .   X    X    X     Guaranteed prominent promotional table  placement at Career Fairs .   X    X    X      Sponsor recognition in electronic event promotions including logo and link.   X    X    X      Sponsor recognition in printed event promotional materials (e.g. signage, posters, banners, flyers). 
 Advertising fee waived for career fair guides.   X    X    X      Priority access to Career Services facilities to conduct interviews for full-time career and internship positions.   X    X    X     Career Services registration fee waived for Career Fairs .   3 Fairs    2 Fairs    1 Fair      Employer representatives included in Career Fair registration fees.    6 Reps    4 Reps    3 Reps      Organized meeting (breakfast or luncheon) with university personnel (may include targeted faculty, department representatives).                Our Current Employer Partners:   Our Academic Year 2020 Employer Partners     Central Intelligence Agency  Ulta Beauty Inc.        about uic content     About Career Services         About Career Services Text      Career Services supports professional development through a combination of interrelated programs and resources.   Dedicated employment & internship resources for students and alumni  Skill development advising  Career Assessments  Networking events & workshops         About UIC         About UIC text      As one of the most ethnically diverse and culturally rich college campuses in the nation, UIC provides students with access to a wide range of disciplines and practices that reﬂect the diversity of a rapidly globalizing world.   Total Enrollment: 31,683 students: 20,783 undergraduates; 7,673 graduates; 3,227 professional students  15 academic colleges: 83 bachelor’s degree programs; 93 master’s degree programs; 64 doctoral degree programs  Recognized as a Military Friendly School with 500  student military veterans  Designated as an Asian American & Native American Pacific Islander-Serving Institution (AANAPISI) & a Hispanic Serving Institution (HIS)              Questions? Please Contact UIC Employer Relations Team      Jaime
    
